00:31:56.060 --> 00:31:59.010
that means it's a wish of God
that you both should play sarod

00:31:59.010 --> 00:32:01.190
or you should be in the music.

00:32:01.190 --> 00:32:04.010
So you can't promote music.

00:32:04.010 --> 00:32:07.730
You can't-- it's
not a commodity.

00:32:07.730 --> 00:32:09.680
So it grows on you.

00:32:09.680 --> 00:32:14.000
And thank god we belong
to the world of sound.

00:32:14.000 --> 00:32:18.430
Because through sound, we
cannot manipulate our life.

00:32:18.430 --> 00:32:21.050
And the other world is language.

00:32:21.050 --> 00:32:23.630
With all due
respect to language,

00:32:23.630 --> 00:32:27.260
I often feel that language
could not create compassion

00:32:27.260 --> 00:32:29.410
and kindness in a human being.

00:32:29.410 --> 00:32:34.840
Even today, we are killing each
other on account of religion.

00:32:34.840 --> 00:32:36.140
It's very sad.

00:32:36.140 --> 00:32:39.470
And my father, he was not
teaching me only music

00:32:39.470 --> 00:32:41.840
but a complete way of life.

00:32:41.840 --> 00:32:45.530
And he often said that all
of us have a common god

00:32:45.530 --> 00:32:48.320
and we are the common race.

00:32:48.320 --> 00:32:50.930
Because I wish
this message should

00:32:50.930 --> 00:32:54.740
had been conveyed by all the
priests of all the religions.

00:32:54.740 --> 00:32:57.330
But every priest has
their own agenda.

00:32:57.330 --> 00:32:59.445
They are also getting
monthly salaries.

00:32:59.445 --> 00:33:02.030
More so, it is up to us.

00:33:02.030 --> 00:33:04.820
We have to realize how
we come to the world

00:33:04.820 --> 00:33:06.890
and how we go away
from this world.

00:33:06.890 --> 00:33:09.080
It's the same passage.

00:33:09.080 --> 00:33:12.334
So we are in the same race.

00:33:12.334 --> 00:33:14.250
SRIDHAR RAMASWAMY: That's
a wonderful message.

00:33:14.250 --> 00:33:16.700
AYAAN ALI BANGASH: And just on
another note, we are not twins.

00:33:16.700 --> 00:33:17.570
I just wanted to clarify.

00:33:17.570 --> 00:33:17.840
AMAAN ALI BANGASH: Yes.

00:33:17.840 --> 00:33:19.589
AYAAN ALI BANGASH:
Just wanted to settle--

00:33:19.589 --> 00:33:20.510
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:33:20.510 --> 00:33:22.010
AMJAD ALI KHAN: --twinish.

00:33:22.010 --> 00:33:23.718
AYAAN ALI BANGASH:
And after I had twins,

00:33:23.718 --> 00:33:25.597
people just think
that we are twins.

00:33:25.597 --> 00:33:26.930
SRIDHAR RAMASWAMY: That's funny.

00:33:26.930 --> 00:33:30.830
AMJAD ALI KHAN:
And also, I wanted

00:33:30.830 --> 00:33:35.450
to share that lot of people
compare Indian music with jazz

00:33:35.450 --> 00:33:37.400
music.

00:33:37.400 --> 00:33:39.560
Yes, jazz musicians
also improvise.

00:33:39.560 --> 00:33:41.480
But they have the
complete freedom

00:33:41.480 --> 00:33:44.660
to use all the 12 notes,
whenever they want.

00:33:44.660 --> 00:33:47.640
But we don't have
that kind of freedom.

00:33:47.640 --> 00:33:50.420
We have to improvise
within the set rule

00:33:50.420 --> 00:33:52.360
of ascending and descending.

00:33:52.360 --> 00:33:55.550
But improvisation is
not such a great thing.

00:33:55.550 --> 00:33:57.770
Even a child can improvise.

00:33:57.770 --> 00:34:00.560
Our salient features of
our Indian classical music

00:34:00.560 --> 00:34:03.140
is slides and glides.

00:34:03.140 --> 00:34:04.940
In Hindi, we call it [HINDI].

00:34:04.940 --> 00:34:06.110
[VOCALIZATION]

00:34:10.280 --> 00:34:14.080
It's a precious gift
from God to our music.

00:34:14.080 --> 00:34:15.767
[VOCALIZATION]

00:34:24.868 --> 00:34:28.500
So ornamentation and
the slides and glides--

00:34:28.500 --> 00:34:33.260
so now, music has
become therapy also.

00:34:33.260 --> 00:34:38.080
A lot of diseases can
be cured by music.

00:34:38.080 --> 00:34:39.980
And plants grow
faster with music.

00:34:39.980 --> 00:34:42.650
Even cattles give
more milk by listening

00:34:42.650 --> 00:34:44.850
to certain kind of music.

00:34:44.850 --> 00:34:46.350
SRIDHAR RAMASWAMY:
That's wonderful.

00:34:46.350 --> 00:34:49.699
You are an inspiration to all
of us with your virtuosity.

00:34:49.699 --> 00:34:51.139
How much do you still practice?

00:34:51.139 --> 00:34:55.395
