certain elements of music.

00:37:13.107 --> 00:37:13.940
Of course, it's him.

00:37:13.940 --> 00:37:15.320
It's the same artist.

00:37:15.320 --> 00:37:23.260
But I think, today, it's him
with that entire journey, which

00:37:23.260 --> 00:37:26.880
he's just sharing
with the world.

00:37:26.880 --> 00:37:30.240
And I think, it's just really
interesting to see that.

00:37:30.240 --> 00:37:33.170
And I think, yes, seeing
even the current situation,

00:37:33.170 --> 00:37:36.380
I don't think he's
made any compromises

00:37:36.380 --> 00:37:39.080
to the traditional
aspect of music.

00:37:39.080 --> 00:37:40.640
Because I don't
think any books said

00:37:40.640 --> 00:37:42.510
how to present classical music.

00:37:42.510 --> 00:37:45.740
I think he's done things a
little bit outside the box.

00:37:45.740 --> 00:37:49.700
And I think it's working very
well with the music lovers,

00:37:49.700 --> 00:37:50.850
as always.

00:37:50.850 --> 00:37:52.250
And this was not my question.

00:37:52.250 --> 00:37:53.816
So my father should answer.

00:37:53.816 --> 00:37:55.524
AMAAN ALI BANGASH:
And you should answer.

00:37:55.524 --> 00:37:56.900
He's our father.

00:37:56.900 --> 00:38:01.700
AMJAD ALI KHAN: You see, because
now the whole voice has become

00:38:01.700 --> 00:38:05.150
so intolerant and impatient.

00:38:05.150 --> 00:38:08.315
And everything should
happen quickly.

00:38:11.100 --> 00:38:15.150
People become musicians to
just perform or to create a CD

00:38:15.150 --> 00:38:18.270
or to go to a reality show.

00:38:18.270 --> 00:38:20.550
And most of the musicians
today, you see, they're

00:38:20.550 --> 00:38:22.530
all standing and performing--

00:38:22.530 --> 00:38:25.340
in such a rush, such a hurry.

00:38:25.340 --> 00:38:32.370
Our tradition is that we have
to sit and play and sing.

00:38:32.370 --> 00:38:37.800
And my father often said
that we must see good points

00:38:37.800 --> 00:38:40.200
at every system of
music, whether it

00:38:40.200 --> 00:38:43.710
is folk music, European
music, any music.

00:38:43.710 --> 00:38:48.030
And in our country, we have
so many states and regions.

00:38:48.030 --> 00:38:50.820
And through a line
of melody, a region

00:38:50.820 --> 00:38:53.300
can be introduced--
a folk music.

00:38:53.300 --> 00:38:55.420
The folk music of Rajasthan--

00:38:55.420 --> 00:38:57.920
[VOCALIZATION]

00:39:22.910 --> 00:39:25.220
So this is folk
music, most ancient.

00:39:25.220 --> 00:39:27.450
Because classical was created.

00:39:27.450 --> 00:39:30.200
It is formalized.

00:39:30.200 --> 00:39:32.580
It wasn't there in--

00:39:32.580 --> 00:39:36.260
so folk music, folk dance,
is the most original form

00:39:36.260 --> 00:39:38.900
of music of any country.

00:39:38.900 --> 00:39:41.480
And then, one day,
I received a message

00:39:41.480 --> 00:39:44.270
from Scottish Chamber Orchestra.

00:39:44.270 --> 00:39:48.200
They wanted me to write a
piece for their orchestra.

00:39:48.200 --> 00:39:52.320
And as we always say,
we don't read and write.

00:39:52.320 --> 00:39:56.510
So I sang in a CD all my
vision and expressions

00:39:56.510 --> 00:39:58.380
for the orchestra.

00:39:58.380 --> 00:40:01.280
Then, I found one conductor--
a British conductor.

00:40:01.280 --> 00:40:02.240
He knew my mind.

00:40:02.240 --> 00:40:03.800
So he wrote everything.

00:40:03.800 --> 00:40:05.990
So now, we have a written score.

00:40:05.990 --> 00:40:07.840
And the piece is
called Samaagam.

00:40:07.840 --> 00:40:11.270
Samaagam means
Conference of Culture.

00:40:11.270 --> 00:40:15.020
So many orchestras of the world,
they are playing my piece.

00:40:15.020 --> 00:40:18.390
This is the first sarod
concerto in the world.

00:40:18.390 --> 00:40:23.150
There are three of us play
with 60, 70 musicians around.

00:40:23.150 --> 00:40:27.950
And I hope, one day, we
could perform that orchestra,

00:40:27.950 --> 00:40:29.064
Samaagam, for you also.

00:40:29.064 --> 00:40:30.480
SRIDHAR RAMASWAMY:
That's amazing.

00:40:30.480 --> 00:40:32.430
That sounds like
an amazing treat.

00:40:32.430 --> 00:40:34.754
I think we have one more
video question from Jocelyn.

00:40:34.754 --> 00:40:35.420
