The laptop is the
guru, in a good way.

00:41:47.070 --> 00:41:50.700
You press, I want
to learn Rag Kidara.

00:41:50.700 --> 00:41:52.230
You press that button.

00:41:52.230 --> 00:41:54.207
And you have 50,000
recordings coming out.

00:41:54.207 --> 00:41:55.290
AMJAD ALI KHAN: Of Kidara?

00:41:55.290 --> 00:41:57.030
AMAAN ALI BANGASH: Of Kidara--
of different musicians.

00:41:57.030 --> 00:41:58.630
So it's a good
thing, at some level.

00:41:58.630 --> 00:42:00.260
It's a good thing.

00:42:00.260 --> 00:42:04.245
And I think, for musicians,
it become a bit tough,

00:42:04.245 --> 00:42:06.890
not for people like him,
but for people like us.

00:42:06.890 --> 00:42:09.570
That when we have a
repertoire of ragas--

00:42:09.570 --> 00:42:12.070
let's say I know 25
ragas or 30 ragas.

00:42:12.070 --> 00:42:14.470
Now, someone is recording it.

00:42:14.470 --> 00:42:16.560
So today, I've played
